docs.abstract: President Trump’s former campaign adviser was convicted of lying to Congress and trying to block a witness in order to impede an investigation into the 2016 Trump campaign.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s former campaign adviser was convicted of lying to Congress and trying to block a witness in order to impede an investigation into the 2016 Trump campaign.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors asked a judge on Monday to sentence Roger J. Stone Jr., President Trump’s longtime friend and former campaign adviser, to up to nine years in prison for lying to Congress and tampering with a witness to prevent investigators from discovering how the 2016 Trump campaign tried to benefit from stolen Democratic documents.

headline.main: Prosecutors Recommend Roger Stone Receive Up to 9 Years in Prison
headline.print_headline: Prosecutors Say That Stone Should Serve 7 to 9 Years

docs.abstract: On the eve of the state’s presidential primary, he arrived with a team of surrogates who will visit polling places on Tuesday.
docs.snippet: On the eve of the state’s presidential primary, he arrived with a team of surrogates who will visit polling places on Tuesday.
docs.lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — In his first rally since the Senate acquitted him on charges that he abused power and obstructed Congress, a triumphant President Trump returned on Monday to New Hampshire, the state where he won his first primary in 2016 and that he hopes to carry in 2020.

headline.main: Trump Travels to New Hampshire to Rally Republicans and Distract Democrats

docs.abstract: Representative Kevin McCarthy, the House minority leader, has made his mark during impeachment by stoking the anger of liberals while keeping the president happy.
docs.snippet: Representative Kevin McCarthy, the House minority leader, has made his mark during impeachment by stoking the anger of liberals while keeping the president happy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Kevin McCarthy of California, the House Republican leader, hails from an era — four years ago — when gaffes could cost a lawmaker a job. In 2015 he lost his shot at the speaker’s gavel after he said the quiet part out loud: The true purpose of Republicans’ two-year inquiry into a deadly 2012 attack on the diplomatic compound in Benghazi, Libya, was to dent Hillary Clinton’s poll numbers.

headline.main: ‘Where Is Kevin?’ McCarthy Finds a Place in the Trump Camp
headline.print_headline: ‘Nice Guy’ Who Provokes the Democrats and Keeps the President Happy
